data.title: Waverley Borough Council
data.meta_description: Information on the UK Parliamentary General Election taking place on Thursday 4 July 2024. Other information includes by-election results, links to Borough Ward maps, details of Waverley polling stations and election expenses information can also be found here.
data.text:
Due to the short notice given for the UKPGE on Thursday 4 July 2024, some polling stations may have changed for this election.

Please view the Situation of Polling Stations Notice on the Godalming and Ash, Farnham and Bordon or Dorking and Horley pages above.

* Temporary polling station for 2 May 2024 election: St Nicolas Church, Church Lane, Cranleigh

** Temporary polling station for all elections/referendums during 2024: Waverley Borough Family Centre, Green Lane, Binscombe

*** Temporary polling station for all elections/referendums during 2024: Church of St John's the Evangelist, St John's Street, Farncombe
